    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-08-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-08-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="530"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d530">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Truman Papers, President’s Secretary’s File</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by President <persName type="from"
                            >Truman</persName> to the Under Secretary of State</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lovett</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">personal and confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-08-16">August 16,
                            1948</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I read the memorandum<note n="1" xml:id="d530fn1">Dated August 11, <ref
                            target="#pg_1300">p. 1300</ref>.</note> regarding the Israel request for
                    $100 million loan and I sincerely hope that there will not be a flat turndown
                    until further consideration has been given by the World Bank.</p>
                <p>Of course, I don’t want any loans made that are not proper for the Bank to make
                    but this situation has all sorts of implications.</p>
                <p>Sometime in the not too far distant future I’d like to have a conversation with
                    you on the subject and incidentally on several other subjects about which I do
                    not want to talk with the Secretary because of their political implications.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>H[<hi rend="smallcaps">arry</hi>] S. T[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >ruman</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
